timeweaver learning history by building networks learning design and technology skip to main content skip to main navigation stanford university school of education learning design and technology home ma programs suse stanford search this site about ldt academics admissions our students faculty & research ldt home home our students master's projects timeweaver learning history by building networks timeweaver learning history by building networks project by molly wilson project year 2011 timeweaver is a map based tool for building and visualizing historical understanding by actively connecting events in a semantic web high school history students create multiple entry points into their knowledge of major historical concepts timeweaver is intended for use in a us history course and plots standardized data sets that correspond with us history curricula as students connect historical events they explain their thinking within the tool and their work is stored the teacher and the class can then view aggregated and individual data and explanations using timeweaver either as a formative evaluation tool or as an avenue to stimulate discussion visit project website our students student portfolios master's projects life after ldt gallery of master's projects 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 2004 2003 2002 2001 2000 1999 stanford university school of education 485 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 3096 tel 650 723 2109 copyright 2012 stanford university all rights reserved site map contact suse admissions helpsu maps & directions suse it axess academic calendar stanford bulletin office of the registrar edmail stanfordwho stanfordyou login connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr website by lyudmila christie suse it
